{
  "text": "Review a meta-analysis with three starting conditions: measures of cognitive outcomes other than IQ are either used non-uniformly across studies or are too diffi cult to combine; IQ variation is not an important component of variation of bias; and the eff ect of historical (lifetime) and momentary phenylalanine concentrations after 6 years of age is seen as one factor only. [CITATION_1] We acknowledge the importance of this meta-analysis, [CITATION_2] and think that the bias due to variation in IQ measures and variation of individual IQ over time should not be underestimated. Additionally, the eff ect of the metabolic control on adult IQ as a measure of neurocognitive outcome should not be overestimated, and in adulthood, the target phenylalanine concentration should be decided by the eff ect of phenylalanine concentrations in adult age.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22309244",
    "[CITATION_2]": "22309244"
